title: High Prevalence of HIV
description: In 2022, 25.9% of Eswatini's population aged 15-49 were living with HIV, one of the highest rates globally.

title: Effective Antiretroviral Therapy Coverage
description: Eswatini achieved a 95% coverage rate for antiretroviral therapy among people living with HIV in 2022, showcasing strong healthcare efforts.

title: High Suicide Mortality Rate Among Males
description: In 2021, Eswatini reported a male suicide mortality rate of 45 per 100,000, indicating significant mental health challenges.

title: High Unemployment Rate with Intermediate Education
description: In 2021, 57.3% of Eswatini's labor force with intermediate education were unemployed, highlighting economic challenges.

title: Low Early Marriage Rate for Women
description: Only 0.1% of women aged 20-24 in Eswatini were married by age 15 in 2022, reflecting progress in gender equality.

title: High Merchandise Exports to Sub-Saharan Africa
description: In 2023, 90.4% of Eswatini's merchandise exports were directed to low- and middle-income economies in Sub-Saharan Africa, indicating strong regional trade ties.

title: High Unemployment Rate
description: Eswatini's total unemployment rate was 34.4% in 2024, according to ILO estimates, reflecting ongoing economic challenges.

title: Low Fisheries Production
description: In 2022, Eswatini produced only 165 metric tons of fish, one of the lowest figures globally, indicating limited fisheries resources.
